SELECT DISTINCT ?wholeLabel WHERE {
  ?part a <ConstituentIRI> .
  ?pr   futuram:refersTo ?part .
  ?stmt futuram:hasPartRelation ?pr .
  ?whole futuram:hasCompositionStatement ?stmt ;
         rdfs:label ?wholeLabel .
} ORDER BY ?wholeLabel
```
INSTANCES (not classes) carry rdfs:label here. If you already know an instance's label, find it directly and read its rdf:type to learn its class. Use this only when you have an instance label; to start from a class a user names, use ex:instancesOfClass instead. The FILTER literal is a placeholder.:

