One row of the data-quality -> rectangular-half-width table: a half-open interval of MEAN data quality [futuram:meanLowerBound, futuram:meanUpperBound) that maps to a futuram:uncertaintyLimit (the relative half-width of the RectangularDistribution). This is how the served uncertainty is DERIVED from the data-quality indicators alone -- limit = band(dataQualityMean), then sigma = limit / sqrt(3). It approximates the FutuRaM reference dataset's hand-authored per-material limit: the source's limit IS a function of the full DQ vector but NOT of any symmetric mean (two vectors with the same mean carry different limits, 0.30 vs 0.35), so a mean-banding reproduces ~68% of rows exactly and collapses the rest by one step. The limit is thus a transparent recompute from quality, not a stored field.:

