```
This system helps to access the following SPARQL endpoints from the FutuRaM:
- FutuRaM fq (query-optimized dataset) (http://localhost:47040/query/sparql): The QUERY-OPTIMIZED fq: dataset over CLASSES. One pattern answers everything: ?class fq:contains [ fq:constituent ?x ; fq:amount ?frac ]. Amounts are already aggregated kg/kg fractions; declare the constituent KIND with rdfs:subClassOf futuram:Element/Material/Component. No tree traversal, no unit normalisation, no manual aggregation.
- FutuRaM composition (baseline composition dataset) (http://localhost:47040/composition/sparql): The BASELINE COMPOSITION futuram:CompositionStatement dataset on INSTANCES. Amounts live in the statement tree: ?whole futuram:hasCompositionStatement ?stmt . ?stmt futuram:hasPartRelation ?pr . ?pr futuram:refersTo ?partInstance ; futuram:hasQuantity/futuram:hasBestValue [ qudt:numericValue ?v ; qudt:unit ?u ]. Units are MIXED (kg/kg vs g/kg). There is NO precomputed aggregate: a constituent's share of a whole several hops up must be obtained by multiplying fractions down each whole->part path, normalising units, and summing paths. This is what the fq: view precomputes.
```
